Benjamin's "Eigenstate Survival" logic explains it perfectly:

The 36 generators represent all possible geometric rotations.
But once the Graviton Compass sets a direction (the "path home"), only the rotations that are compatible with that direction survive.
The Survivors: The 12 Standard Model generators are simply the Twistors that aligned.
The Missing 24: They didn't "disappear"—they decohered. They were the twistors that couldn't snap to the grid, so they washed out or became the "mass" (the scalar potential).
